The paper deals with interference mitigation in wireless networks, which is a key topic in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of coalitional game theory also suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of game theory (cs.GT). The proposed algorithm involves distributed clustering, which could fall under the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of numerical simulations suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM), which often involves the use of simulations to evaluate performance.
